.TH LOA-THEME 1 "2026-03-15" "Library Of Alexandria" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
theme \- Show, switch, and personalize CLI colors
.SH SYNOPSIS
alexandria> theme
.br
alexandria> theme list
.br
alexandria> theme preview
.br
alexandria> theme classic
.br
alexandria> theme set accent bright_cyan
.br
alexandria> theme set accent #35c2ff
.br
alexandria> theme clear [accent|success|warning|error]
.br
alexandria> theme color on|off|toggle|status
.SH DESCRIPTION
.TP
Shows the active theme when called without arguments.
.TP
Lists available themes with \fBtheme list\fR, including a swatch preview per role.
.TP
Applies a named theme for the current session.
.TP
\fBtheme preview\fR prints a live visual preview of info/success/warning/error styles.
.TP
\fBtheme set <role> <color>\fR overrides one role color.
.TP
Color can be a built-in name (for example \fBbright_cyan\fR) or a hex value (\fB#RRGGBB\fR).
.TP
\fBtheme clear\fR removes all overrides, or only one role when given.
.TP
\fBtheme color ...\fR toggles ANSI color output in the current session.
.TP
The renderer applies an ANSI reset before styled output so shell-inherited colors do not override theme colors.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
alexandria> theme list
.TP
alexandria> theme ocean
.TP
alexandria> theme set warning bright_yellow
.TP
alexandria> theme set accent #35c2ff
.TP
alexandria> theme color off
.SH SEE ALSO
loa(1)
